Building a brand requires an emotional response to come through the selected details. 

During our consultation calls we speak with the client about the overall aesthetic and emotion they want to emulate. Our client @monalavinia desired a audacious pop of color to exude the energy she brings to her passion of fitness while emulating the grit and grind in the day-to-day process.

This was the finalized moodboard created to kick off the start of building her brand identity.

A brand with a warm yet bold presence magnifying confidence to help their clients represent their best self right where they’re at in the moment while wearing @unmasteredco.

The vision for @unmasteredco brand identity is about a community that meets you in the spaces between who you’ve been and who you’re becoming through wellness. 

A work in progress but still ________.
• worthy
• growing
• learning
• trying
• evolving
• shining
• being
• deserving
• transforming
• blooming
• becoming

A brand is more than a logo, it’s a depicted emotion that the consumer gets when interacting with the brand while encompassing our five senses. The overall aesthetic visual should be aiming to hit these questions:

How would the brand tastes?
How does the brand sound?
How would the brand feel?
How would the brand look?
How would the brand smell?

If we can’t answer those questions through the visual of the moodboard our work has not been completed. We strive for an emotional reaction from the various aesthetics presented from our clients prior to the process of creating a logo design. It’s about the spark in feeling the motive behind what we create.

Looking to work with us? Inquire via the link in bio!
